      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;At level 70 I prefer to Solo than to group -- Groups and Raids take up a LOT OF TIME -- whereas when I solo I can get right down to business. I usually don't group but I do Raids and I simply hate raids --They take a long time to set up and actually get going. I have done raids in Time, &amp;nbsp;Uqua, Ikkinz1-4, MPG raid Trials, and RS raids -- hated them all. But if you want gear and spells you have no other avenue and I find this is really bad that SOE only forces you to raid.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I feel that I should have the ability to get&amp;nbsp;my 69-70 spells and High end gear other than by raiding. Why can't these spells and gear be given out to soloers who do particularly difficult tasks? &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The current rewards for soloing are really pathetic. --- also please REMOVE THE NO DROP from GLOWING and GREATER RUNES -- so we can at least buy them instead of spending 6 hours in a raid. -- I really hate the amount of time raiding takes up -- and would so much prefer to do hard tasks solo. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Soloers should have the opportunity -- ( even if more difficult and takes longer) to acquire 69 and 70 spells and upper end gear without being compelled to devote their free time to Raids. At the high end of this game you have to raid and that soaks up a lot of time until EQ seems more like a full time job than a game you play for fun. &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
