      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Jiga-jiga posted an idea in another thread that I thought was interesting...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;He suggested a NO DROP item with a 1-charge Dire Charm that could be used by soloers to get a temporary, NPC hunting partner.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I see all kinds of exploits in that, but...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What about hirelings?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Maybe a solution to the soloing problem is to go to a Guild Master and HIRE NPC's to group with.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Yes, they would SUCK and their AI might be poor. But it could very well provide the needed support for certain classes to solo.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;For example, a cleric goes to hire a warrior. Essentially, it because a Warrior pet for the cleric. Comes with a certain level of gear. You let it die without rez, lose faction with the guild master and may not be able to hire another. Takes no loot, but does take a percent of XP.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Perhaps you can "hire" only Tank or Healer and only one at a time.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Would be EXPENSIVE (they take no loot) and should be, maybe, 3-5 levels BELOW the person hiring them. Relatively poorly equipped. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Warrior would have tons of HP, no disciplines, marginal gear. This case is pretty straightforward, EQ already has limited AI for warrior pets.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Healers would be tougher - just healing, no buffs.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Casters could be done, but spell availability, spell selection and mana management might require too much of the existing AI.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Virtually everything else needed for soloing is already available elsewhere - Snare devices (expensive), invis potions, etc.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It's really the tanking and the healing....&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
