    <item>
      <title>Re: Improvements to soloing/tasks (January Summit)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=51839#M51839</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The task system in Everquest was a great step in the right direction to allow something to do "with in an hourto play &amp;nbsp;and still accomplish something." This great idea was to give reward in the form of cash and experiance, but less so than grouping experiance or cash to make sure that grouping was still the prime choice of experiance in Everquest. Yet, this system has been plauged with problems with how long it takes to actually accomplish some tasks, the rewards given for the time, and the overall difficulty of the tasks for some classes to accomplish.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I believe the tasks in and of themselves are fine "as is", but the time constraints are spawned via specifics for quest completion when killing mobs. For example the Droga quests have you slay a specific type of goblin and a moderate number. The problem comes down with classes that lack basic utility spells to miander around that dungeon to specifically find those goblins to accomplish the task. This bogs down the player into either clearing any goblin in hopes of finding the type of goblin she must slay inorder to accomplish her task, buy invis potions to miander around in hopes of finding the specific goblins, or just plain giving up. These tasks were designed for completion within an hour or so, but the specifics in this case bog downt he player for much longer than that. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;In this case changing the specific names of the goblins to "any goblin", would allow the player to slay her specific number of goblins for the quest completion within a short period of time. This would equate the low xp reward and the low monitary reward in terms of I believe true worth for the task system. This example applies to alot of the tasks where specific mobs shouldn't be used, as they create a "camp" for the specific mobs to spawn. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;People enjoy having long term goals, but also want to accomplish short term goals quickly. In terms of quickness I mean an hour or so for a small reward. I would like to ask that this please be looked into as to make the task system truely shine in both ideal and function. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Another aspect of Everquest is the faction system and the questing system as a whole. The common usage with the factions system&amp;nbsp;in Everquest has been go slaughter thousands of green cons with area effect spells for hours on end to maximize efficiency. In all honesty when I envision an intrepid hero trying to make a name for herself trying to become welcomed into a hostile city&amp;nbsp; is doing favors for the locals, protecting the local's interest, and proving herself through sword, fist, or magic on the enemies of the people.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;In this format rather than forcing the "grind" aspect of factioning, an intrepid adventurer tasks a job or in this case a task from a local that is indifferent to outward politics and wants to use a hired mercenary to accomplish a goals. Instead of giving experiance and coin, factions and experiance are given. Eventually with enough tasks the reputation of the intrepid&amp;nbsp;adventurer could give her a more welcome responce by the populous and thus open up new oppertunities for adventure and fame and riches. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;To define this in a game mechanics sort of deal. My thoughts are converting the task system into a faction system that introducing a step stone for kill on sight people or those with dubious or apprehensive faction to gain favor with the city as an intrepid hero. This would I believe strongly add to the flavor of being "evil" or "good" and allow players to immerse themselves into defending their allies. This can be a simple start such as just killing off a small incursion of orc centurions or delivering messages to guard outposts in other zones and other such small "favors." These can scale eventually into harder tasks, or if higher level the person can take these tasks that yield better faction and experiance for the city. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Once a high faction is achieved within the city this leaves new oppertunities for the adventurer to become entagled in political quagmires, stories of espionage, and political assassinations for bigger rewards. People are always looking for fun trinkets such as illusion items or usefull gadgets that make their gaming experiance a little bit better such as invisibility items. Grouped tasks here can be quests that give rewards to add to the flavor of Everquest. Or even soloible quests that give small trinkets that are multi-staged such as the Qeynos Badge series can be expanded upon through expansion material as politics change and new powers are introduced to the gaming world. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I believe that offering quests in Everquest that scale and grow with the intrepid heroes of Norrath is to keep the feeling of "old world" alive and well. The epic quests brought back alot of the old world flavor by bringing alot of us back home. Yet our homes and those places of interest to us are stangated into an ancient time frame that has long since past. Very few seem aware of changes or don't ever seem to age. Legendary kings seem to standstill, forever frozen in a time period long since past. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I believe by updating older content with mixing newer content and offering ways to bridge and bring back the flavor of feeling like players have&amp;nbsp; home they are loyal to is a good way to go. Norrath still has plenty of intrique and mystery left with many factions opposing one another. I believe further their storylines and allowing Everquest players to fully delve back into the older content and mixing it with newer content will bring back memories of slaying orc pawns and allow players to feel as though they are truly the heroes of a people or a scourge upon the land. I appreciate anytime spent reading this.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Anyway reposted here for inclusion into this thread I guess if you're going to reuse this material at the summit? I'll do a much more complex write up this quest issue and so forth latter =p&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sun, 02 Jan 2005 02:55:55 GMT</pubDate>
