    <item>
      <title>Re: Improvements to soloing/tasks (January Summit)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=51636#M51636</link>
      <description>The XP rate on these needs to be some meaningful fraction of what can be obtained in a group. Presently (at level 70) I find that they are about 1/2 AA/hour, compared to a typical 2-4 AA/hour in pick-up XP group (slightly more in a group of "regulars"). While I can accept SOE's reasons for encouraging grouping, the ratio is so low that this is hardly a "meaningful" option for those that cannot regularly group, for whatever reason. In my opinion, a reasonable "set point" for solo XP activities would be around half that from a solid group. The rate of XP gain should be scaled with level to stay at the same point relative to grouped XP, and should be "the same" for all classes, including those that typically cannot "solo" for XP.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;LDoN points are interesting, but unless the LDoN rewards are reworked, they are outdated and obsoleted in most cases for a large fraction of the player base. Even the HP+40 augs have faded in attractiveness for many. For the few "must have" items remaining (&lt;i&gt;i.e., &lt;/i&gt;GRC, some general-purpose LDoN spells, DPoC, a couple specific non-level-fading augs) I agree that there needs to be incentive to "do" LDoNs again, especially for lower-level players. (Higher-level players have issues beyond LDoN rewards, with 1/2 AA per level 70 expedition being ridiculously low.) Resolution of those issues should, in my opinion, be done outside of the Task system.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The faction issues with Tasks need to be addressed. In some cases, completing a Task lowers the faction required to "safely" access the Taskmaster that gives you the quest.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Tasks to raise specific factions, either as an alternative to mass genocide of "greenies," or for factions that are difficult or impossible to improve, would be very interesting. Even though I don't roleplay, I would, for example, love to be able to go back and just stroll NToV with a friend, just to see it again and share memories. (Issues with faction-based exploits ignored in that last comment.) Such Tasks should be identified if they yielded less XP that other Tasks that required comparable time/effort.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Tasks should not involve dispelling mobs as this heavily penalizes those without "the best" gear, which are often the players most able to benefit from an alternative to grouping play.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Summoning mobs, in my opinion, are not an issue. There are plenty of "soloable" mobs out there that do not summon. Even those that do, if the rewards are great enough, become soloing targets (&lt;i&gt;e.g., &lt;/i&gt;NC named for runes).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alternatives to "soloing for XP" should, in my opinion, be expanded. Quests of any wide and significant value seem to have evaporated from the landscape after the Coldain Shawl/Ring quests (there were significant access and/or reward problems with things like Power of the Planes, Aid Grimel, BiC, GoD tongues, etc.). These should be available to a wide range of players without the need for raid encounters (which remove the VP quests from the discussion).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Edit -- One of the issues with "soloing" is the potential for death. Risk is good, within reason. With Tasks sending you to basically unused zones, the penalties for running out of HP are much higher than in populated zones. One possible way to mitigate this would be to allow players to drag corpses across zone lines, allowing them to bring their corpse to a more populated area for a rez. I haven't thought through possible exploits that might limit this.&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by itchyban on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;12-29-2004&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;11:36 AM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
